---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Insulation Officer VIC | Atherstone, NatHERS 7-Star Estate Builds | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Insulation for Officer VIC — NatHERS 7-star new-build batts (Atherstone, Officer Rise), ceiling top-ups on mid-2000s estates, media-room acoustic, cavity pump-fill on Princes Hwy-era homes. VEU rebate-eligible where applicable."
  canonical="https://beaconsfieldinsulation.com.au/officer/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Officer &middot; Atherstone &middot; Officer Rise</span>
      <h1>Insulation in <span class="accent">Officer</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Officer is two markets in one suburb &mdash; the new NatHERS 7-star
        estates (Atherstone, Officer Rise, Heritage Springs-adjacent) where
        first-fit walls and ceiling are the conversation, and the older
        Princes Highway-era homes where retrofit ceiling and cavity pump-fill
        deliver the comfort upgrade.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free assessment</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Officer</span>
      <h2>The Officer insulation story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>NatHERS 7-star new builds &mdash; first-fit at framing stage.</h3>
        <p>
          Atherstone and Officer Rise estates are largely 2018&ndash;2026 builds
          to NatHERS 7-star standard. That means R5.0+ ceiling, R2.7 total
          system walls, R2.0 underfloor (where applicable), and anti-condensation
          sarking under the roof. We work with several Officer-area volume
          builders supplying and installing the wall and ceiling batts at
          frame stage, sized correctly to the actual stud cavities and
          neatly fitted around windows, services and downlight rough-ins.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Officer Estate (mid-2000s) ceiling top-ups.</h3>
        <p>
          Officer Estate homes built around 2005&ndash;2015 typically have
          ceiling insulation at R3.0&ndash;R3.5 &mdash; meets the standard of
          the day but well below current R5.0&ndash;R7.0 expectations. A
          straightforward R-value top-up (lay R3.5 batts on top of existing
          to reach R6.5&ndash;R7.0) is one of our most common Officer jobs.
          $3,500&ndash;$5,500 for a 180m&sup2; home, often eligible for the
          VEU rebate if the original install rated R2.0 or lower.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Heritage Princes Highway homes &mdash; retrofit work.</h3>
        <p>
          The older Princes Highway / Old Princes Highway / Stoney Creek Road
          Officer homes (1970s&ndash;1990s brick veneer and weatherboard)
          have the same retrofit opportunities as Beaconsfield: empty wall
          cavities for pump-fill, suspended timber floors for underfloor batts,
          and often ceiling insulation under R2.0 or none at all. VEU
          eligibility is high.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Townhouse and dual-occ &mdash; NCC F5 party walls.</h3>
        <p>
          Officer has a growing dual-occupancy and townhouse market across
          the estate releases. Most need NCC F5 party-wall compliance
          (Rw + Ctr &ge; 50) which is delivered through acoustic batts
          (Knauf Earthwool Acoustic or Bradford Sound Screen) installed in
          a resilient-channel or staggered-stud wall system. We coordinate
          with the builder on installation timing and on-site compliance
          testing.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Officer jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>NatHERS 7-star first-fit wall + ceiling batts on new build ($4K&ndash;$8K supplied + installed)</li>
          <li>Officer Estate ceiling R3.5 &rarr; R6.5 top-up ($3.5K&ndash;$5.5K, often VEU-eligible)</li>
          <li>Pre-2000 cavity pump-fill on Princes Highway-era brick veneer ($4.5K&ndash;$7K)</li>
          <li>NCC F5 party-wall acoustic batts in townhouse builds ($180&ndash;$280/m&sup2;)</li>
          <li>Underfloor on heritage Officer weatherboard ($3K&ndash;$5.5K)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/beaconsfield/">Beaconsfield</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/pakenham/">Pakenham</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-lakes/">Cardinia Lakes</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/heritage-springs/">Heritage Springs</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cardinia-shire/">All Cardinia Shire</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Officer insulation assessment.</h2>
        <p>New build first-fit or estate retrofit. NatHERS 7-star compliant. VEU lodged for you.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
